    <content type="html"><![CDATA[<p>Since the version of redis-server in Ubuntu is too old, so we need to install it from a PPA repository.</p>

<figure class='code'><figcaption><span>Install redis-server from Chris Lea&#8217;s PPA</span></figcaption><div class="highlight"><table><tr><td class="gutter"><pre class="line-numbers"><span class='line-number'>1</span>
<span class='line-number'>2</span>
<span class='line-number'>3</span>
<span class='line-number'>4</span>
<span class='line-number'>5</span>
<span class='line-number'>6</span>
<span class='line-number'>7</span>
<span class='line-number'>8</span>
</pre></td><td class='code'><pre><code class='sh'><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>sudo add-apt-repository ppa:chris-lea/redis-server
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>sudo apt-get update
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>sudo apt-get install redis-server
</span><span class='line'><span class="nv">$ </span>redis-cli
</span><span class='line'>redis 127.0.0.1:6379&gt; INFO
</span><span class='line'>redis_version:2.4.15
</span><span class='line'>...
</span><span class='line'>...
</span></code></pre></td></tr></table></div></figure>

